{"title_page": "Debra Shopteese", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Debra Shopteese|timestamp=20200420033356|year=2020|month=April|day=20|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Debra Shopteese|date=20 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{short description|American judge}}\n'''Debra Shopteese''' is a Massachusetts judge. She was the first [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] to sit on the Massachusetts District Court.<ref name=patch/><ref name=alumni/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://web.archive.org/web/20150107171121/http://www.mass.gov/governor/administration/jnc/nominations-to-the-district-court.html|title=Nominations to the District Court|date=2015-01-07|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life and education==\nShoptese grew up in Kansas and is of [[Sauk people|Sac]] and [[Meskwaki|Fox]] descent.<ref name=patch/> She attended [[Kansas State University]], earning a bachelor of science degree in 1983, and then [[Northeastern University School of Law]] where she was a member of the class of 1986.<ref name=patch/><ref name=martin/><ref name=mlw/>\n\n==Legal career==\n\nShopteese was first admitted to the Massachusetts bar in 1988.<ref name=martin/><ref name=mlw/> She spent her entire pre-judicial career of 24 years as a [[public defender]] at the Committee for Public Counsel Services.<ref name=patch/><ref name=alumni/><ref name=mlw/> This time included serving as the Attorney-in-Charge for the Roxbury Defenders Division from 1999 to 2011.<ref name=patch/><ref name=mlw/> As a lawyer, she was mentored by [[Massachusetts Supreme Judicial Court]] Chief Justice [[Roderick Ireland]].<ref name=patch/>\n\nAt the time of her appointment to the District Court, she taught criminal trial advocacy at Northeastern University.<ref name=patch/><ref name=mlw/> She was appointed by Governor [[Deval Patrick]] and sworn into the post on September 21, 2011.<ref name=patch/><ref name=alumni/><ref name=mlw/>\n\nShe previously sat on the Massachusetts Juvenile Court.<Ref name=patch/> In 2012, she served in the [[Boston Municipal Court]].<ref name=mlw/> {{Asof|2015}}, Shopteese was assigned to the Roxbury District Court.<Ref name=martin/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2018/10/17/man-accused-hitting-cyclist-jamaica-plain-charged/qf1Adshdgm5c4HByqoqt2M/story.html|title=Man accused of hitting cyclist in Jamaica Plain arraigned - The Boston Globe|last=Staff|first=Emily Sweeney Globe|last2=October 17|website=BostonGlobe.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20|last3=2018|last4=Comments|first4=11:09 a m Email to a Friend Share on Facebook Share on TwitterPrint this Article View}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n*[[List of first women lawyers and judges in Massachusetts]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=alumni>{{cite web | url = https://calendar.northeastern.edu/event/alumniae_of_color_panel_5028 | title = Alumni/ae of Color Panel | publisher = Northeastern University | accessdate = April 5, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=martin>{{cite web | url = https://www.martindale.com/attorney/debra-shopteese-689919/ | publisher = Martindale-Avvo | accessdate = April 6, 2020 | title = Debra Shopteese }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=mlw>{{cite web | url = https://masslawyersweekly.com/judicial-profiles/shopteese-debra/ | title = SHOPTEESE, DEBRA | publisher = Mass. Lawyers Weekly | date = January 27, 2012 | accessdate = April 6, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n<Ref name=patch>{{cite news | url = https://patch.com/massachusetts/jamaicaplain/jamaica-plain-resident-becomes-first-native-american-c7dec16a16 | title = JP Resident Becomes First Native American Judge in Mass.\n| first = Andrew | last = McFarland | date = September 22, 2011 | accessdate = April 6, 2020 | website = [[Patch.com]] }}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n[[Category:living people]]\n[[Category:Sac and Fox people]]\n[[Category:People from Jamaica Plain]]\n[[category:Kansas State University alumni]]\n[[category:Northeastern University School of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:American women judges]]\n[[Category:Massachusetts state court judges]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Debra Shopteese|timestamp=20200420033356|year=2020|month=April|day=20|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Debra Shopteese|date=20 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{short description|American judge}}\n'''Debra Shopteese''' is a Massachusetts judge. She was the first [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] to sit on the Massachusetts District Court.<ref name=patch/><ref name=alumni/>\n\n==Personal life and education==\nShoptese grew up in Kansas and is of [[Sauk people|Sac]] and [[Meskwaki|Fox]] descent.<ref name=patch/> She attended [[Kansas State University]], earning a bachelor of science degree in 1983, and then [[Northeastern University School of Law]] where she was a member of the class of 1986.<ref name=patch/><ref name=martin/><ref name=mlw/>\n\n==Legal career==\n\nShopteese was first admitted to the Massachusetts bar in 1988.<ref name=martin/><ref name=mlw/> She spent her entire pre-judicial career of 24 years as a [[public defender]] at the Committee for Public Counsel Services.<ref name=patch/><ref name=alumni/><ref name=mlw/> This time included serving as the Attorney-in-Charge for the Roxbury Defenders Division from 1999 to 2011.<ref name=patch/><ref name=mlw/> As a lawyer, she was mentored by [[Massachusetts Supreme Judicial Court]] Chief Justice [[Roderick Ireland]].<ref name=patch/>\n\nAt the time of her appointment to the District Court, she taught criminal trial advocacy at Northeastern University.<ref name=patch/><ref name=mlw/> She was appointed by Governor [[Deval Patrick]] and sworn into the post on September 21, 2011.<ref name=patch/><ref name=alumni/><ref name=mlw/>\n\nShe previously sat on the Massachusetts Juvenile Court.<Ref name=patch/> In 2012, she served in the [[Boston Municipal Court]].<ref name=mlw/> {{Asof|2015}}, Shopteese was assigned to the Roxbury District Court.<Ref name=martin/>\n\n==See also==\n\n*[[List of first women lawyers and judges in Massachusetts]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=alumni>{{cite web | url = https://calendar.northeastern.edu/event/alumniae_of_color_panel_5028 | title = Alumni/ae of Color Panel | publisher = Northeastern University | accessdate = April 5, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=martin>{{cite web | url = https://www.martindale.com/attorney/debra-shopteese-689919/ | publisher = Martindale-Avvo | accessdate = April 6, 2020 | title = Debra Shopteese }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=mlw>{{cite web | url = https://masslawyersweekly.com/judicial-profiles/shopteese-debra/ | title = SHOPTEESE, DEBRA | publisher = Mass. Lawyers Weekly | date = January 27, 2012 | accessdate = April 6, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n<Ref name=patch>{{cite news | url = https://patch.com/massachusetts/jamaicaplain/jamaica-plain-resident-becomes-first-native-american-c7dec16a16 | title = JP Resident Becomes First Native American Judge in Mass.\n| first = Andrew | last = McFarland | date = September 22, 2011 | accessdate = April 6, 2020 | website = [[Patch.com]] }}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n[[Category:living people]]\n[[Category:Sac and Fox people]]\n[[Category:People from Jamaica Plain]]\n[[category:Kansas State University alumni]]\n[[category:Northeastern University School of Law alumni]]\n[[Category:American women judges]]\n[[Category:Massachusetts state court judges]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "ClaudeDavid", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added verified sources.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Debra_Shopteese"}
